description.plain:
linked up with Nnamdi through Instagram and we were just bouncing off beats and ideas. the first verse and the hook of the song was actually done since summer ‘17 with Emir Hermono but the continuation of the project was further halted until I eventually found the perfect voice for the last verse.

nobody else would have served that beat justice if it wasn’t for Laze. had a couple memorable sessions at the blue room getting it just right.

fun fact:
this song opened the performance during We The Fest ‘17, before anyone knew what the song was.

description.plain:
‘Waktu Tiba’ tells a story of a man, possibly A.Nayaka himself, that is sick of his relationship with his girlfriend.

The song progresses from the first time he met her in Bali. Then suddenly he had enough of it, saying that it’s all his fault but she won’t have that discussion with him. It made him even furious.

Then in the second verse, he reveals that actually his girlfriend did have some issues.

So yeah, now he’s thought about it for a long time and made his decision, to tell her to get the fuck out of his life.

this was one of those tracks that we knew instantly how it was gonna. Indy (TRIP TRVP) and I have been working alotta times and he rolls through the studio often. we did Fuccboy, Powder Pablo, and some more in the vault. this track tho, was inspired after watching the 2013 The Wolf of Wall Street.

money, growing on me…

fun fact:
this was the last song recorded for the album

description.plain:
The beginning song plays around an 808 piano style beat with lots of reverb and bass. Carakarantina translates to “Quarantine way” from Indonesian.

This theme plays out across the entire album with a central focus on how being in lockdown makes us feel isolated and feelings of losing our marbles.
